 can help forge new concepts better adjusted to an emergent situation. Addressing tensions between working class experience and norms of the academy, his father’s coma, antiwar protests, the growing disaffection of the white working class, the neoliberalization of the university, climate denialism, and his sister’s experience with workers shifting to Trump, Connolly shows how engaged intellectuals become worthy of the events they encounter.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aMemoryzUnited States. 0aRecollection (Psychology). 0aThought and thinking. 0aWorking class white peoplezUnited States. 0aWorking classzUnited States. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / History & Theory.2bisacsh  aEvent.  aFoucault.  aGilles Deleuze.  aProust.  aWriting.  acreative thought.  ademocracy.  afascism.  aideology.  amemory.  amimesis.  atemporality.  athe working class.  auniversity life.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2022 Englishz978311099451308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2022z9783110994407oZDB-23-PLW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertFordham University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311075166640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781531500252?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781531500252423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781531500252/original  a978-3-11-075166-6  Fordham University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  a978-3-11-099389-9  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishb2022  a978-3-11-099451-3  EBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2022 En